claim.claim-text:
A method for analysis of plurality of network transactions in a communication network consisting of a first set of nodes characterized by monitoring a plurality of sub-transactions constituting said network transactions, the method comprising processor implemented steps of:
a. classifying a second set of nodes hosting said sub-transactions into a first set of layers, each layer containing a third set of nodes with similar functionalities;
b. capturing a network transaction data at each node of each classified first set of layer and storing it in a repository in the network in test environment;
c. generating and storing a plurality of transaction flow signatures depicting hierarchical flow of said network sub-transactions amongst said classified layers and associated performance at each node based on captured network transaction data in test environment;
d. capturing a network transaction data of at least one network transaction in the network in a real time environment from the first set of layers facilitating at-least one sub-transaction of said network transaction;
e. identifying at least one transaction flow signature from the stored transaction flow signatures matching the network transaction by correlating network parameters and transaction parameters; and
f. generating a diagnostic report indicating a layer-wise nodal anomalies and associates performance constraints in the communication network for the network transaction analyzed through identified transaction flow signature using metrics comparisons for multiple layers, multiple sessions and multiple individual layers

A distributed system for analysis of plurality of network transactions in a communication network, the distributed system comprising:
a) a plurality of communication nodes, each communication node comprising a data capturing module;
b) a plurality of processing servers coupled to a repository storing network transaction data, said processing servers further comprising at least one of the following processing modules:
i. a layer configuration module to classify a second set of nodes into a first set of layers;
ii. a network transaction data capture module to capture network transaction data at each classified layer;
iii. a transaction signature generation module to generate a plurality of transaction signatures;
iv. a network transaction monitoring engine configured to: sort network transaction data for at least one network transaction on the basis of a first set of layers, identify at least one transaction flow signature for the said network transaction; and
v. a metric analysis engine to generate a diagnostic report indicating a layer-wise nodal anomalies and associated performance constraints in the communication network.
